{
  "text": "Since attachment of HEK293T cells to culture surfaces is not very strong, vector production is more difficult to perform in roller bottles and transfection conditions in these devices have to be carefully optimized for keeping cells attached. In this context, Patel et al. [CITATION_1] could show that the overexpression of alpha-v and beta-3 integrin by HEK293 led to an increased cell adhesion allowing efficient LV vector production in roller bottles. However, this approach requires the use of recombinant HEK293 cells overexpressing integrin.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "82815657"
